For detailed license information, please refer to: http://www.lexvo.org/legal.html -->  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://lexvo.org/id/iso639-3/nap">   <rdf:type rdf:resource="lvont:Language" />   <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="xsd:string" xml:lang="en">Southern Italian (Dialetti italiani meridionali), or Napoletano-Calabrese, is a group of Italo-Dalmatian Romance dialects spoken in Southern Lazio, Southern Marche, Abruzzo, Molise, Campania, Basilicata, Apulia, and Northern Calabria. Part of a language continuum, they are all mutually intelligible and are often referred to as Neapolitan languages (based on Naples' historic role as capital of the region). According to Ethnologue, the dialects are grouped as Napoletano-Calabrese and are given the status of language. Some consider the dialects simply as Italian dialects affected by a samnite substratum.</rdfs:comment>   <rdfs:label rdf:datatype="xsd:string"
